formula_7
This equation has two linearly independent solutions.
Up to scalar multiplication, is the solution subject to the condition as .
The standard choice for the other solution is the Airy function of the second kind, denoted Bi(&quot;x&quot;). It is defined as the solution with the same amplitude of oscillation as as which differs in phase by :

formula_8
